title: Dr. Suzanne Humphries
cleaned_text:
Dr. Humphries earned her BA degree in Physics from Rutgers University in Camden, NJ. She earned her medical degree from Temple University Medical School in Philadelphia, PA.

Dr. Humphries spent eleven years in conventional practice in Internal Medicine and Nephrology in Maine, but left in 2011. Since then, she's continued research into medical issues like vaccines, immunity and functional medicine. She continues to lecture around the world on topics related to vaccination, infant immunity, vitamin C and more.

Dr. Humphries authored Dissolving Illusions: Disease, Vaccines and The Forgotten History and more recently, Rising From the Dead.

For more information, go to drsuzanne.net.
